[2] China: new EVD antiviral drug
Date: 1 Sep 2014
Source: SCMP [edited]
http://www.scmp.com/news/china/article/1582834/ebola-virus-approved-mainland-emergency-use-only


China's 1st drug against EVD has obtained manufacturing approval for emergency use, a military newspaper reports. The drug, named JK-05, was developed by Professor Wang Hongquan with the Institute of Microbiological Epidemiology under the Academy of Military Medical Sciences, according to the PLA News.

"JK-05 is a micro-molecular chemical, and its pharmacological mechanism is to selectively contain the RNA polymerase of the Ebola virus to inhibit virus replication," Wang told the newspaper.

Wang's study showed JK-05 resisted the replication of Ebola cells in experiments and animal tests. The drug, after 5 years of study, has passed pre-clinical testing and the clinical safety test. However, the drug currently is strictly limited for emergency use only, Wang said.

