[3] Prevention, suspected cases

Nigeria: fatal case in Abuja
----------------------------
1 Sep 2014: (iREPORTS-NG) A suspected Ebola virus disease (EVD) patient has [died] in one of the biggest government-owned hospitals in Abuja, Asokoro General Hospital, in the nation's capital city, barely 3 weeks after another suspected patient died in a private hospital [there]. The death, which was said to have occurred last weekend [30-31 Aug 2014] has already caused serious panic in the Federal Capital Territory (FCT). In a statement released yesterday [31 Aug 2014], spokesperson of FCT Health Secretariat Badaru Salisu Yakasai said the results of the tests conducted on the deceased have yet to either confirm or refute claims that the patient died of EVD.
http://ireports-ng.com/2014/09/01/suspected-ebola-patient-dies-in-abuja-hospital-doctors-nurses-placed-under-surveillance

Sweden: negative
----------------
1 Sep 2014: (MSN News NZ) A man suspected of being infected with the deadly ebolavirus ravaging several African countries has tested negative in Sweden, local health officials say. "We analysed the tests and can say there is no sign whatsoever that the patient was suffering from EVD," a statement said. The man, a foreign national who travelled to Sweden from an EVD-affected area last week, was hospitalised on Sun [31 Aug 2014].
http://news.msn.co.nz/worldnews/8899171/suspected-ebola-case-in-sweden-official

Sudan: hemorrhagic fever case in Darfur
---------------------------------------
31 Aug 2014: (StarAfrica) The minister of health affairs for the Darfur Regional Authority, Firdos Abdel Rahman Yousif, denied reports of the deadly Ebola virus disease in El Geneina, capital of West Darfur State. The Sudan News Agency quoted the minister as saying the suspected case had come from Abeche in Chad. The patient suffered from hemorrhagic fever, began taking treatment from the health center, and was then transferred to a hospital in El Geneina, she claimed. ...
http://en.starafrica.com/news/sudan-bans-reporting-on-ebola.html

