[There have not been any reports of EVD or any other hemorrhagic fever in Chad, but yellow fever (YF) needs to be excluded, because there was an outbreak of YF in 2012 in Darfur, Sudan, which also affected Chad, and 6 million people were vaccinated in Darfur in 2013; see ProMED-mail: Yellow fever - Africa (12): Sudan (Darfur) 20130302.1567578.

It is highly unlikely that EVD has arrived in the region, as I don't think there is much human through traffic all the way from Bamako in Mali, just north of the Guinean border, and the Chad-Sudan border, around 4000 km (2500 miles) further east by the trans-African highway (see map at: http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/0/03/Map_of_Trans-African_Highways.PNG), nor many air passengers from West Africa via Khartoum. If anyone has information to the contrary, ProMED-mail would be glad to receive it. - Mod.JW

A HealthMap/ProMED-mail map can be accessed at: https://promedmail.org/promed-post?place=2740572,54.]
